quran[18]{c,v,t,f}:
  53,46,"From a sperm-drop when it is emitted"
  53,47,"And that [incumbent] upon Him is the other [i.e., next] creation."
  53,48,"And that it is He who enriches and suffices"
  54,37,"And they had demanded from him his guests, but We obliterated their eyes, [saying], "
  54,38,"And there came upon them by morning an abiding punishment."
  54,39,"So taste My punishment and warning."
  55,31,"We will attend to you, O prominent beings.{1}",footnotes:1:Specifically two:  mankind and jinn.
  55,32,"So which of the favors of your Lord would you deny?"
  55,33,"O company of jinn and mankind, if you are able to pass beyond the regions of the heavens and the earth, then pass. You will not pass except by authority [from Allāh]."
  56,22,"And [for them are] fair women with large, [beautiful] eyes,"
  56,23,"The likenesses of pearls well-protected,"
  56,24,"As reward for what they used to do."
  57,13,"On the [same] Day the hypocrite men and hypocrite women will say to those who believed, ",footnotes:1:To where light was acquired, i.e., in the worldly life.
  57,14,"They [i.e., the hypocrites] will call to them [i.e., the believers], ",footnotes:1:By hypocrisy or by falling into temptations.
  57,15,"So today no ransom will be taken from you or from those who disbelieved. Your refuge is the Fire. It is most worthy of you, and wretched is the destination."
  58,7,"Have you not considered that Allāh knows what is in the heavens and what is on the earth? There are not three in a private conversation but that He is the fourth of them,{1} nor are there five but that He is the sixth of them - and no less than that and no more except that He is with them [in knowledge] wherever they are. Then He will inform them of what they did, on the Day of Resurrection. Indeed Allāh is, of all things, Knowing.",footnotes:1:Through His knowledge of them and their secrets.
  58,8,"Have you not considered those who were forbidden from private conversation [i.e., ridicule and conspiracy] and then return to that which they were forbidden and converse among themselves about sin and aggression and disobedience to the Messenger? And when they come to you, they greet you with that [word] by which Allāh does not greet you{1} and say among themselves, ",footnotes:1:This is in reference to the Jews who would greet the Muslims with the words "Death be upon you," rather than "Peace."
  58,9,"O you who have believed, when you converse privately, do not converse about sin and aggression and disobedience to the Messenger but converse about righteousness and piety. And fear Allāh, to whom you will be gathered."